Next Step: Design and Build a Proxy Provider Service with Dynamic Health Management
Objectives:
Continuous Proxy Discovery and Testing

Develop a background worker/service that:
Periodically fetches fresh proxy lists from reliable sources.
Continuously tests proxies for connectivity, anonymity, and Google accessibility.
Maintains a live, prioritized proxy pool where the freshest and most reliable proxies appear at the top.
Marks proxies as unhealthy promptly if they fail tests or trigger anti-bot defenses.
Proxy Pool Persistence & Metadata

Use a database or fast cache (Redis, etc.) to store the proxy list with metadata:
Last tested timestamp
Success/failure history and scores
Current health status (active, banned, cooldown)
Enable quick retrieval of the best proxy for use.
Integration with Scraping Service

Modify your scraping workers to:
Request a proxy from the proxy provider service before or when starting a driver session.
Detect when a CAPTCHA or block page appears during scraping.
Report back immediately the proxy causing the issue.
Upon receiving a bad proxy report, the proxy provider:
Marks the proxy as unhealthy or removes it temporarily.
Supplies a new fresh proxy to the scraping worker.
The scraping worker switches to the new proxy seamlessly, without losing scraping progress (e.g., resumes from last known state, last page, or last successful query).
Failover & Resilience

Include logic for failover proxy switching:
If the current proxy fails or is reported bad, switch proxies immediately.
Avoid re-using recently banned proxies until cooldown expires.
Metrics and Monitoring

Track proxy usage, failure rates, and scraping success.
Alert when proxy pool runs low or performance drops.
Why this architecture?
Efficiency: Workers don’t waste time validating proxies themselves.
Scalability: Proxy provider can be scaled independently, handling thousands of proxies.
Reliability: Fresh, tested proxies ensure less downtime and fewer captchas.
Agility: Fast proxy switching keeps scraping continuous, minimizing lost data or time.
Maintainability: Clear separation of concerns between proxy management and scraping logic.